.TH SHUTDOWNTIMER 1 "March 2026" "1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
shutdowntimer \- schedule system shutdown with login screen messaging
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shutdowntimer
.RI [ OPTION ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shutdowntimer
is a desktop utility for scheduling system shutdowns, restarts, sleep,
and hibernation actions \(em either as a countdown or at a specific time.
.PP
It also allows administrators to set a message on the login screen before
a scheduled shutdown, so users are informed in advance. The message is
automatically cleared after the next login.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-auto\-clear
Run in headless mode: clear the login screen message and exit.
This is invoked automatically by the systemd user service scheduled
when the "auto-clear after next login" option is enabled.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/issue
Universal TTY login message. ShutdownTimer writes a clearly marked block
inside this file and removes it on clear.
.TP
.I /etc/sddm.conf.d/shutdown-timer-msg.conf
SDDM greeter message drop-in configuration. Created when SDDM is detected.
Removed on clear.
.TP
.I /etc/lightdm/lightdm.conf.d/shutdown-timer-msg.conf
LightDM greeter message drop-in configuration. Created when LightDM is
detected. Removed on clear.
.TP
.I ~/.config/systemd/user/shutdowntimer-autoclear.service
Systemd user service that runs
.B \-\-auto\-clear
once at the next login. Created when auto-clear is enabled, removed after
it fires.
.SH PRIVILEGED OPERATIONS
Writing to
.I /etc/issue
and display manager configuration files requires administrator privileges.
ShutdownTimer uses PolicyKit (
.BR polkit (8)
) to request elevated permissions. The user is prompted for their
password once per session.
.PP
When running inside a Flatpak sandbox, privilege escalation is handled
by the
.B shutdowntimer-helper
D-Bus system service.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemctl (1),
.BR shutdown (8),
.BR polkit (8),
.BR sddm (1),
.BR lightdm (1)
